#
# Trivy vulnerability exceptions (SCA — filesystem scan, CRITICAL + HIGH).
#
# This file is the ONLY sanctioned way to suppress a CRITICAL/HIGH finding.
# It is deliberately empty: no exception is active. When one is unavoidable,
# it must be time-bounded so a suppression cannot rot into a permanent hole.
#
# Policy (the 14-day class):
#   - Every entry MUST carry an `exp:YYYY-MM-DD` expiry no more than 14 days
#     out. On that date the suppression lapses and the gate re-reds — forcing
#     a re-decision rather than silent, indefinite acceptance.
#   - Every entry MUST name a tracking reference (issue / advisory) and a
#     one-line reason on the comment line above it.
#   - A no-fix-available CVE is not automatically exempt: prefer bumping,
#     pinning, or removing the dependency. Suppress only to buy the 14-day
#     window while the real fix lands.
#
# Format (trivy .trivyignore, one CVE id per line, optional trailing `exp:`):
#   # <reason> — tracked in <issue/url>
#   CVE-XXXX-NNNNN exp:2026-01-15
#
# (no active exceptions)
